<br>
   I'm deeply sorry if we truely offended you folks.  That was not our intention, nor do I believe it was ToN's intention to 'roll over' you.  Unfortunately this is something that should have been discussed previous to ToN leaving the NToV agreement, or at least announced before it became an issue, that ToN considered Vulak to be 'open game' whenever he was up.<br>
<br>
  When the NToV agreement was written I truely don't believe that Vulak was considered to be a part of it.  Vulak is an entirely different scale of mob compared to the rest of the game.  Requires more force, better discipline and generally higher level toons than anything else in ToV.  Just because the RoV is located in NToV does not make it by default part of the NToV agreement, just as Eashen and Ikitar are part of NToV but not part of the agreement.  That agreement was formed to keep guilds from &quot;stepping on each other toes&quot;, allowing one guild to roam free in NToV while others went after targets in rougly the same difficulty tier outside NToV.  Just as Eashen and Ikitar are &quot;easier&quot; than the mobs past Aary, so is RoV &quot;harder&quot;.<br>
<br>
The point is that RoV is a different scale of encounter.  This isn't justification of ToN's actions as a guild, just personal sentiment.  However I felt the same way before ToN even left the rotation (and note that ToN had not been taking our listed turn in the rotation for at least two cycles before we formally left).<br>
<br>
It seems like the biggest issue that folks are having is that this time through ToN leadership didn't ask for the all clear well in advance of heading in, thus we were not told before gathering that Isen did not want us in there.  As far as this is concerned, all I can say is that us asking in the past does not necessarily set precident where we have to ask every single time.  I am sorry that our past actions led you to believe we would &lt;always&gt; ask permission first before moving on the RoV  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
